value.title: Biden in 2005 said nixing the filibuster 'upsets the constitutional design' and would 'eviscerate the Senate'
value.excerpt: Sen. Ben Sasse, R-Neb., spent over an hour on the Senate Wednesday night reading a 2005 speech from President Biden verbatim  where he said eliminating the filibuster would “eviscerate the Senate.”

value.title: Trump quizzed four Ohio GOP Senate prospects at fundraiser: Report
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump spoke Wednesday night with four GOP candidates running to fill retiring Ohio Sen. Rob Portman’s seat in an intense meeting that one onlooker likened to the “Hunger Games,” according to a report.

value.title: Biden says GOP state voting legislation makes 'makes Jim Crow look like Jim Eagle'
value.excerpt: President Biden said Republicans’ state voting legislation "makes Jim Crow look like Jim Eagle" during his first formal press conference on Thursday.

value.title: Biden says it's his 'expectation' to run for reelection in 2024, makes Trump quip
value.excerpt: President Biden says it's his "expectation" that he'll run for reelection in 2024.

value.title: Ron Johnson: Biden admin seems 'deaf, dumb and blind' to border crisis, dangers to migrants
value.excerpt: The Biden administration is "deaf, dumb, and blind" to the dangers posed on the migrants as they attempt to cross the southern border, Sen. Ron Johnson, R-Wis., told "Fox & Friends" on Thursday, addressing the crisis that prompted GOP lawmakers to visit the border.

value.title: Biden’s claim that 'dogs may help cure cancer' draws Twitter reactions
value.excerpt: President Biden is known to be a lover of dogs – but did he recently give canines more credit than they deserve?

value.title: Arizona’s Ducey calls Harris the ‘worst possible choice’ to fix border
value.excerpt: Gov. Doug Ducey, the Arizona Republican, didn’t mince words Wednesday shortly after he learned that President Biden was tapping Vice President Harris to oversee the effort to resolve the crisis at the U.S.-Mexico border.

value.title: Biden Thursday press conference slated for 1:15 pm Eastern in the East Room
value.excerpt: President Biden will hold his first news conference as commander-in-chief Thursday at 1:15 p.m. EST in the East Room.

value.title: Kamala Harris to hold discussion with Bill Clinton on 'empowering women and girls,' igniting criticism
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris will hold a joint discussion on "empowering women and girls" with former President Bill Clinton, who has been accused of sexual misconduct by multiple women.

value.title: Bernie Sanders not ‘comfortable’ with Trump Twitter ban
value.excerpt: Senator Bernie Sanders said recently that he’s not “comfortable” with former President Trump’s Twitter ban, arguing it could lead suppression of users across the political

value.title: GOP Colorado Rep. Boebert accuses Biden of 'politicizing' Boulder shooting
value.excerpt: Rep. Lauren Boebert, R-Colo., accused President Biden on Tuesday of “politicizing” the mass shooting at a Boulder, Colorado grocery store that left 10 people dead after he called for a nationwide ban on assault weapons.

value.title: Senate Republicans demand second hearing for Biden DOJ pick Gupta after 'misleading' comments’
value.excerpt: Republicans on the Senate Judiciary Committee have called for President Biden’s pick for associate attorney general, Vanita Gupta, to return for a second round of hearings to answer for "misleading statements."

value.title: Kayleigh McEnany blasts Biden administration for 'unprecedented' lack of media access to border
value.excerpt: Former White House press secretary Kayleigh McEnany slammed the Biden administration Tuesday for what she described as an "unprecedented" lack of media access to the border.

value.title: Trump coy about social media comeback but says Twitter did him ‘a favor’
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump on Monday declined to confirm reports that he’s poised to make a social media comeback, but said that in the meantime, he’s enjoying emailed press

value.title: Meghan McCain apologizes for aiding Trump's 'racist' COVID rhetoric after being called out by John Oliver
value.excerpt: "The View" co-host Meghan McCain issued an apology on Monday after she was called out by "Last Week Tonight" host John Oliver for comments she made about rhetoric tying the coronavirus outbreak to China.

value.title: Biden regularly consults with Barack Obama on a 'range of issues', Psaki says
value.excerpt: White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki on Monday said that President Biden maintains “regular” communication with President Barack Obama on a number of issues.

value.title: MSNBC's Brian Williams touts ad from disgraced Lincoln Project linking Trump to Atlanta spa shootings
value.excerpt: MSNBC anchor Brian Williams touted a new ad released by the disgraced Lincoln Project last week that tried to tie former President Donald Trump's rhetoric about the coronavirus to the March 16 Atlanta spa shootings.

value.title: Biden HHS to turn San Diego Convention Center into migrant shelter
value.excerpt: The Biden Administration is turning the San Diego Convention Center into a temporary shelter to support unaccompanied children seeking asylum in the United States.

value.title: AOC endorses controversial Democrat who compared voting for Biden to eating 's***'
value.excerpt: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y., endorsed controversial Democrat Nina Turner running for a vacant Ohio congressional seat who compared voting for President Joe Biden to eating feces.

value.title: Biden world praises Clinton adviser who reportedly ignored Weinstein warning, dismissed Tara Reade's claims
value.excerpt: Biden world sang the praises of Democratic strategist Adrienne Elrod on Sunday after a glowing profile on her work with Biden's team.

value.title: McCarthy hires Trump’s White House political director to lead operation
value.excerpt: House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy hired one of former President Trump's top staffers to lead his political operation, a source familiar with the hire told Fox News.

value.title: Trump slams Biden over border 'crisis', accused him of causing 'death and human tragedy'
value.excerpt: President Biden said Sunday that he intends to travel to the southern border "at some point," telling reporters that he is in no rush to visit because "I know what's going in those facilities."

value.title: Trump returning to social media with 'his own platform' in 2-3 months: adviser
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump will be back on social media in the near future with his own service, according to one of his senior advisers.

value.title: Biden response to border crisis 'isn't incompetence', but 'is by design', Tom Homan tells Mark Levin
value.excerpt: President Biden "sold out this country to the progressive left to win an election," former Immigration and Customs Enforcement Acting Director Tom Homan told "Life, Liberty & Levin" in an interview airing Sunday.

value.title: Trump boosts Julia Letlow in Louisiana House race to succeed her late husband
value.excerpt: Former President Trump urged his supporters to back Julia Letlow Saturday in the special election House race in Louisana to succeed her late husband, Luke, who died after contracting coronavirus.

value.title: Harris, in apparent swipe at Trump, says people ‘with the biggest pulpits’ spewed hate toward Asian Americans
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris, speaking in Atlanta in the wake of this week's mass shooting, said that people in power had been "scapegoating Asian Americans,” an apparent reference to Donald Trump.

value.title: Baltimore prosecutor Marilyn Mosby, once championed by VP Harris, now target of federal investigation
value.excerpt: State's Attorney for Baltimore Marilyn Mosby, whose career was boosted by Vice President Kamala Harris, is now facing a federal investigation with a wide breadth of subpoenas.

value.title: Biden stumbles multiple times, falls as he scales Air Force One stairs
value.excerpt: President Biden stumbled twice and fell as he scaled the stairs to Air Force One on Friday at Joint Base Andrews.

value.title: Biden administration 'importing' coronavirus into Texas by not securing border: Gov. Abbott
value.excerpt: Texas Gov. Greg Abbott, R., told "America's Newsroom" Friday that the Biden administration is effectively importing coronavirus into the United States by not adequately securing the southern border.

value.title: Texas wax museum moves Trump statue because visitors kept hitting it: report
value.excerpt: The owner of Louis Tussaud’s Waxworks in San Antonio said the museum removed a statue of former President Trump because too many visitors punched and scratched the figure, a report said.
